<section xml:id="templates-array-list_appendix-array-list-header"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">

  <title>Appendix - Array List Header Implementation</title>

  <p>The final implementation of ArrayList as a header file is shown below. Note that all the code
    for the ArrayList class is included in this file. There will not be an <pf>ArrayList.cpp</pf> file.</p>

  <p>Other than the lack of module/export definitions, and the inclusion of a header guard, the
    primary difference between the header version and module version is the lack of <pf>using namespace std</pf> in the
    header version. Whereas a module can use <pf>using</pf> without polluting the namespace of code that <pf>imports</pf>
    the module, a header file should avoid using <pf>using</pf> directives to prevent potential naming
    conflicts.</p>

